#1 Instalar python-setuptools
#2 instalar pip: sudo easy_install pip
#3 Instalar virtualenv
#4 Intsalar VirtualEnvWrapper 
#########----MODIFICAR LOS SIGUIENTE----#########

1st, ensure you're installing with sudo:


2nd, append the following lines to your .bashrc file

nano ~/.bashrc
-----    
AGREGAMOS ESTO AL ARCHIVO
export WORKON_HOME=$HOME/.virtualenvs
source /usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.sh
---------
3rd, reload your profile

source ~/.bashrc


#**------ Para usar Postgres:
sudo apt-get install python-dev